# DNS Records for n8n Deployment

> **Checklist: Update these values before running the playbook!**
> - Change all example domains (e.g., {{ n8n_domain }}) to your real domain.
> - Set your server's public IP for `n8n_public_ip`.
> - Set the correct MX target for `dns_locale_mx_target`.
> - Change all example emails (e.g., example@example.com) to your real admin/notification email.
> - Replace `p=...` in DKIM with your generated public key.

## A/CNAME Record
- **Type:** A or CNAME
- **Name:** {{ n8n_domain }}
- **Value:** {{ n8n_public_ip }}

## MX Record
- **Type:** MX
- **Name:** {{ n8n_domain }}
- **Value:** {{ dns_locale_mx_target }}

## SPF Record (TXT)
```
{{ n8n_domain }}. IN TXT "v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com ~all"
```

## DKIM Record (TXT)
```
default._domainkey.{{ n8n_domain }}. IN TXT "v=DKIM1; k=rsa; p={{ dkim_public_key }}"
```

## DMARC Record (TXT)
```
_dmarc.{{ n8n_domain }}. IN TXT "v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; rua=mailto:{{ dmarc_rua_email }}"
```
